 uncovers the role the city played in the regional, local, and "global" economies during the eight centuries of its existence. Sidebotham analyzes many of the artifacts, botanical and faunal remains, and hundreds of the texts he and his team found in excavations, providing a profoundly intimate glimpse of the people who lived, worked, and died in this emporium between the classical Mediterranean world and Asia.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aExcavations (Archaeology)xEgyptxBarānīs. 0aExcavations (Archaeology)zEgyptzBarānīs. 0aExcavations (Archaeology)zEgyptzBarānīs. 0aInternational tradexHistoryxTo 1500. 0aInternational tradexHistoryyTo 1500. 0aPort citiesxHistoryxTo 1500xEgypt. 0aPort citieszEgyptxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aSpice tradexHistoryxTo 1500xEgyptxBarānīs. 0aSpice tradezEgyptzBarānīsxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aSpice tradezEgyptzBarānīsxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aTrade routesxHistoryxTo 1500xEgyptxBarānīs. 0aTrade routeszEgyptzBarānīsxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aTrade routeszEgyptzBarānīsxHistoryyTo 1500. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520948389423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520948389.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles